Cord progression
	Any combination of cords built from a scale

	Each note has a cord built from them

	C - major		1
	D - minor		2
	E - minor		3
	F - major		4
	G - major		5
	A - minor		6
	B - diminished	7

	1 - 4 - 5
		Se toma una escala mayor y se toman acordes de 1 - 4 - 5

		C D E F G A B

		1 - C major -> C E G
		4 - F major -> F A C
		5 - G major -> G B D  

	1 - 5 - 6 - 4
		C D E F G A B

		1 - C major -> C E G
		5 - G major -> G B D
		6 - A minor -> A C E
		4 - F major -> F A C

	1 - 6 - 2 - 5
		C D E F G A B

		1 - C major -> C E G
		6 - A minor -> A C E
		2 - D minor -> D F A
		5 - G major -> G B D

		